1
00:00:00,584 --> 00:00:02,044
In the previous episode,

2
00:00:02,169 --> 00:00:04,087
the match between
Nankatsu and Shutetsu

3
00:00:04,254 --> 00:00:05,255
ended in a draw.

4
00:00:05,422 --> 00:00:06,590
Now everyone
is getting ready for

5
00:00:06,715 --> 00:00:07,758
the national tournament.

6
00:00:07,925 --> 00:00:09,718
The best players from
the local schools' teams

7
00:00:09,885 --> 00:00:11,470
will be chosen
to form a new team

8
00:00:11,595 --> 00:00:12,804
that represents the city.

9
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:14,223
From the Nankatsu School,

10
00:00:14,223 --> 00:00:17,100
Tsubasa, Taro and Ryo
were chosen.

11
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:20,270
Meanwhile, Roberto requested
to Tsubasa's parents

12
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:21,897
to allow him
to go to Brazil

13
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:23,273
so Roberto can train him

14
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:25,400
and make him
the best player of all time.

15
00:00:26,193 --> 00:00:28,570
Shocked by the news,
Tsubasa happily agrees

16
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:31,573
and tells Roberto that he
will go with him to Brazil

17
00:00:31,657 --> 00:00:33,659
once the national
tournament is over.

18
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:36,161
It's a once in
a lifetime opportunity

19
00:00:36,328 --> 00:00:37,287
for Tsubasa.

20
00:00:39,957 --> 00:00:44,920
[opening theme]

21
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:24,853
Episode 10:
Kojiro Appears.

22
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:25,646
MEIWA 4 ICHIEDA 0

23
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:26,355
MEIWA 4 ICHIEDA 0
Stop him! Don't let Kojiro near the goal!

24
00:02:26,355 --> 00:02:28,774
Stop him! Don't let Kojiro near the goal!

25
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:29,733
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

26
00:02:32,778 --> 00:02:34,488
Their attacks are
so pathetic.

27
00:02:34,613 --> 00:02:35,781
They can't stop me!

28
00:02:36,365 --> 00:02:39,284
If you want to fight me,
it has to be to the death!

29
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:42,120
So arrogant! I won't let you
score anymore goals!

30
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:44,081
No way!

31
00:02:44,248 --> 00:02:45,958
You idiots!

32
00:02:52,381 --> 00:02:53,006
What in the world is

33
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:54,132
wrong with you, Kojiro?

34
00:02:54,258 --> 00:02:55,300
Why would you do that?

35
00:02:55,425 --> 00:02:56,635
-My leg!
-You're the worst!

36
00:02:56,635 --> 00:02:58,679
You don't have to hurt
others to play soccer!

37
00:02:58,804 --> 00:02:59,388
That's not right!

38
00:02:59,555 --> 00:03:00,639
Just shut up!

39
00:03:00,764 --> 00:03:03,684
Soccer is only for
the strongest players!

40
00:03:03,809 --> 00:03:04,893
You're miserable!

41
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:06,270
This was supposed to be

42
00:03:06,395 --> 00:03:08,772
a practice match
before the trials!

43
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:11,775
I won't let you hurt
anymore players!

44
00:03:11,817 --> 00:03:13,026
The game is over!

45
00:03:16,655 --> 00:03:17,656
Captain!

46
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,283
-Hm?
-Don't you think

47
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:20,492
it's enough for today?

48
00:03:20,784 --> 00:03:21,785
Excuse me?

49
00:03:21,994 --> 00:03:23,161
You're not planning
on listening

50
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:24,538
to those fools,
are you?

51
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,793
Well, let's see then...

52
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,671
how you manage to qualify
without me.

53
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:33,839
-What?
-What?

54
00:03:34,006 --> 00:03:35,340
If you don't like
how I play,

55
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:36,633
then that's fine by me.

56
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:38,552
I'll stay on the bench
from now.

57
00:03:38,677 --> 00:03:41,096
Someone else can be
the captain for all I care.

58
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:42,222
But, Captain...

59
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:45,893
I'm Kojiro Hyuga,
and this is how I play.

60
00:03:46,018 --> 00:03:47,394
Victory is for the strong!

61
00:03:47,519 --> 00:03:49,980
You must be aggressive
if you want to win!

62
00:03:54,526 --> 00:03:55,527
Tsubasa!

63
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:59,406
Excellent shot, Tsubasa!

64
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:01,533
Thank you!
Now is your turn, Taro!

65
00:04:05,537 --> 00:04:07,998
I wonder if it was
the right call.

66
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:10,167
Huh?

67
00:04:12,211 --> 00:04:14,087
The captain leaves
in two weeks.

68
00:04:14,796 --> 00:04:17,049
And if I take Tsubasa
to Brazil with me...

69
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:20,135
his mother would be
all alone in Japan.

70
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:22,095
I can't do that to her.

71
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:24,473
Even if he chose to
go to Brazil with me,

72
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:25,599
without any doubt,

73
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:26,892
-he would miss his childhood
-Roberto?

74
00:04:27,017 --> 00:04:28,018
with his parents.

75
00:04:28,227 --> 00:04:29,353
-Roberto!
-Huh?

76
00:04:30,354 --> 00:04:31,396
-Oh!
-What's the matter?

77
00:04:31,522 --> 00:04:32,898
You looked really worried.

78
00:04:33,232 --> 00:04:34,858
Oh it's...
It's nothing.

79
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:36,360
How about a little break?

80
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:37,528
-Okay.
-Okay.

81
00:04:37,611 --> 00:04:38,862
Ryo, how is it going?

82
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:43,200
What's wrong, Ryo?

83
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:44,743
We're just getting
started here!

84
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:49,623
What?
Did you get tired already?

85
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:52,000
Your grandpa works all day
and he doesn't get tired.

86
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,293
Oh, that's harsh!

87
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,087
Even my grandpa
takes a break!

88
00:04:55,212 --> 00:04:57,339
I just need five minutes
to catch my breath!

89
00:04:57,339 --> 00:04:58,340
That's okay.

90
00:04:58,465 --> 00:05:00,717
But for sure you won't
get one tomorrow.

91
00:05:00,843 --> 00:05:02,469
Why are you so mean to me?!

92
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:04,263
Tsubasa, Taro and you

93
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:06,515
were chosen after
the first eliminatory round,

94
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:08,392
and we'll make sure
you stay.

95
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,394
So you better do your best!

96
00:05:10,936 --> 00:05:11,895
That's right.

97
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,897
Tsubasa and Taro
are surely gonna pass,

98
00:05:14,064 --> 00:05:16,358
but you need more training.
We have to make sure.

99
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:18,360
That's so mean! I thought
you believed in me!

100
00:05:18,485 --> 00:05:19,361
Yes, we do!

101
00:05:19,361 --> 00:05:21,530
We just want to make sure
you stay in the team.

102
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:23,282
That's why we
want to help you

103
00:05:23,282 --> 00:05:24,700
reach your potential.

104
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:28,203
Thanks everyone!

105
00:05:30,789 --> 00:05:32,165
I hope he gets to stay.

106
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:33,292
He'll make it.

107
00:05:33,292 --> 00:05:34,293
Yeah!

108
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:35,502
SHUTETSU VS. MATSUKAWA

109
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:36,420
He stole the ball!

110
00:05:36,545 --> 00:05:39,256
Defenders! Don't let him
score another goal!

111
00:05:39,381 --> 00:05:40,382
Uhh...

112
00:05:40,591 --> 00:05:41,633
Humph!

113
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:42,968
Oh!

114
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:47,347
SHUTETSU VS. MATSUKAWA

115
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:48,348
SHUTETSU VS. MATSUKAWA
I did it!

116
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:48,473
SHUTETSU VS. MATSUKAWA

117
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:49,433
SHUTETSU VS. MATSUKAWA
You're really good!

118
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:49,474
You're really good!

119
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:53,061
This is not even close
to what Nankatsu will face

120
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,855
on the national tournament.

121
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,400
Oh no! He managed
to get past him!

122
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,359
Captain!

123
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:00,986
Tsubasa, next time,

124
00:06:01,111 --> 00:06:02,905
we'll be playing
on the same team.

125
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:04,740
Here!

126
00:06:04,907 --> 00:06:05,866
Got it!

127
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:08,285
No, it can't be!

128
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:10,370
Genzo won't let them score!

129
00:06:15,334 --> 00:06:16,585
That's the end of the match!

130
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,212
I'm... I'm sorry!

131
00:06:25,219 --> 00:06:26,303
Hey, guys,

132
00:06:26,303 --> 00:06:28,972
this new team is supposed
to be really strong, right?

133
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:31,558
If Tsubasa, Taro,
and Genzo are in it,

134
00:06:31,683 --> 00:06:33,602
I'm sure we'll win
the national tournament.

135
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:36,271
Yeah! With them,
we will win for sure!

136
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:37,856
I wouldn't be so sure.

137
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:40,692
All the teams participating
in the tournament

138
00:06:40,776 --> 00:06:41,693
are very good.

139
00:06:41,777 --> 00:06:42,778
Oh, I get it!

140
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:44,363
You're saying that because
you've played with

141
00:06:44,363 --> 00:06:45,614
most of them before, right?

142
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:46,990
Exactly.
For example,

143
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:48,408
against the team
from Chiba...

144
00:06:49,326 --> 00:06:51,036
They train every day
on the beach,

145
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:52,579
and they are really strong.

146
00:06:55,499 --> 00:06:56,375
players there are.

147
00:06:57,835 --> 00:07:01,171
The Naniwa team from Osaka
has the tallest players,

148
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:02,214
and because of that,

149
00:07:02,339 --> 00:07:04,550
they are experts at
intercepting the ball.

150
00:07:04,883 --> 00:07:08,178
The Hakata team from Fukuoka
has members of all ages

151
00:07:08,303 --> 00:07:10,389
and they take advantage
of what they learn

152
00:07:10,514 --> 00:07:12,474
and they are
very unpredictable.

153
00:07:13,475 --> 00:07:16,395
Wow! There sure are many
different kinds of teams.

154
00:07:16,395 --> 00:07:17,229
Yeah, many.

155
00:07:17,396 --> 00:07:19,231
If we manage to go to
the national tournament...

156
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:21,233
our strongest opponent
will surely be

157
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,860
the Meiwa team
from Showa...

158
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:25,195
Its captain's last name
is Hyuga.

159
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:26,405
He is really strong...

160
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:29,700
with skills that almost
match Tsubasa's skills.

161
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:30,701
-Huh?
What?!

162
00:07:30,826 --> 00:07:32,244
That's impossible!

163
00:07:32,369 --> 00:07:34,037
There's no way
he matches Tsubasa!

164
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:35,372
He's the only one
that managed

165
00:07:35,497 --> 00:07:36,915
to score a goal to Genzo!

166
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,375
Kojiro is a striker.

167
00:07:38,709 --> 00:07:39,835
A very different type.

168
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:41,420
His nature and game style

169
00:07:41,545 --> 00:07:43,213
is very different
than yours.

170
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:45,632
Kojiro Hyuga,

171
00:07:46,425 --> 00:07:47,843
from the Meiwa team.

172
00:07:56,727 --> 00:07:58,687
I can't keep up
much longer.

173
00:08:02,107 --> 00:08:03,150
Hi, Genzo!

174
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:05,527
I suppose you're
heading home, right?

175
00:08:06,403 --> 00:08:07,738
What happened to you, Ryo?

176
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:09,281
You look a little beaten up.

177
00:08:09,281 --> 00:08:10,282
Am I right?

178
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:11,283
Just shut up!

179
00:08:11,408 --> 00:08:13,285
It's only because
I trained really hard

180
00:08:13,285 --> 00:08:14,786
for the try outs, okay?!

181
00:08:14,912 --> 00:08:17,080
But without any talent,
the effort is pointless.

182
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:19,166
Come here and
I'll show you my talent!

183
00:08:22,085 --> 00:08:23,086
What's the matter?

184
00:08:24,505 --> 00:08:26,298
It's nothing.
Don't worry, I'm fine.

185
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:34,306
You know what,
Roberto?

186
00:08:34,515 --> 00:08:36,475
I can't wait to meet
that kid, Kojiro.

187
00:08:36,475 --> 00:08:38,685
Taro told me
he's nothing like you.

188
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:41,104
But I'll tell you,
just like him...

189
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:43,398
all the other players
are very different.

190
00:08:43,565 --> 00:08:44,608
I believe you.

191
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:46,568
I'm sure that in Brazil

192
00:08:46,735 --> 00:08:48,403
the players are
very different too.

193
00:08:49,071 --> 00:08:50,614
If you come to Brazil,
you won't get back

194
00:08:50,739 --> 00:08:53,075
until you've become
a professional player.

195
00:08:53,367 --> 00:08:54,034
Yeah!

196
00:08:54,201 --> 00:08:56,036
No matter what, I'll be
a professional player!

197
00:08:56,203 --> 00:08:57,704
That's my dream
and I won't stop

198
00:08:57,829 --> 00:08:59,081
until I finally get it!

199
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:00,874
Then I'll be able to play
soccer every day!

200
00:09:00,999 --> 00:09:04,002
Yes, but first, you must
qualify for and win

201
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:05,462
the national tournament.

202
00:09:05,754 --> 00:09:08,298
Otherwise, you won't get to
come with me to Brazil.

203
00:09:08,423 --> 00:09:09,758
I'll win
the national tournament!

204
00:09:10,634 --> 00:09:11,969
It's not that easy.

205
00:09:17,266 --> 00:09:18,267
Look closely.

206
00:09:24,398 --> 00:09:26,900
A professional must
be able to do this.

207
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:28,485
Uh-huh.

208
00:09:28,902 --> 00:09:31,530
Of course, you're still
very young to do this.

209
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:33,907
Your bones haven't
fully developed yet.

210
00:09:34,116 --> 00:09:36,535
If you try this,
you'll only hurt yourself.

211
00:09:36,702 --> 00:09:37,995
Yeah, I get it.

212
00:09:38,287 --> 00:09:39,288
By the way...

213
00:09:39,621 --> 00:09:40,581
About Genzo...

214
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:42,374
I want to tell you
that I noticed

215
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:45,002
he was slightly limping
on one of his legs.

216
00:09:45,127 --> 00:09:46,128
Huh?

217
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:50,716
And so, the day
of the first practice match

218
00:09:50,841 --> 00:09:53,010
for the Nankatsu team
arrived.

219
00:09:53,719 --> 00:09:55,637
Out of the 30
chosen young men,

220
00:09:55,721 --> 00:09:58,432
only 15 will be able to
stay and play

221
00:09:58,599 --> 00:09:59,766
in the national tournament

222
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,685
representing
the Nankatsu city.

223
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:04,021
Okay, we will divide
the group

224
00:10:04,146 --> 00:10:05,480
in the following way,

225
00:10:05,564 --> 00:10:06,773
since we have
a lot of players

226
00:10:06,899 --> 00:10:08,275
from the Shutetsu team.

227
00:10:08,275 --> 00:10:08,817
Pay attention!

228
00:10:08,817 --> 00:10:09,276
Pay attention!
SHUTETSU VS. MIXED

229
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:09,401
SHUTETSU VS. MIXED

230
00:10:09,401 --> 00:10:12,905
SHUTETSU VS. MIXED
Team A will be composed of just Shutetsu players.

231
00:10:12,905 --> 00:10:13,197
SHUTETSU VS. MIXED

232
00:10:13,197 --> 00:10:15,199
SHUTETSU VS. MIXED
The rest will form the other team.

233
00:10:15,199 --> 00:10:15,449
SHUTETSU VS. MIXED

234
00:10:15,532 --> 00:10:17,534
You heard that?
A match against Shutetsu!

235
00:10:17,701 --> 00:10:19,912
We haven't seen them
since the last match.

236
00:10:20,037 --> 00:10:23,040
Yeah! And we will play so
that the 15 players selected

237
00:10:23,207 --> 00:10:25,334
are only from Team Shutetsu!

238
00:10:25,417 --> 00:10:26,460
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

239
00:10:32,424 --> 00:10:34,885
If you're ready,
then we will begin!

240
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:42,100
All right,

241
00:10:42,226 --> 00:10:44,478
looks like it's time
to have some fun.

242
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:47,397
Okay, let's go team!

243
00:10:47,564 --> 00:10:48,899
We won't let you!

244
00:10:49,024 --> 00:10:49,983
We will be the ones
to play

245
00:10:50,108 --> 00:10:51,360
on the national tournament!

246
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,361
Listen up!

247
00:10:52,486 --> 00:10:54,905
Just pass the ball around
to confuse them!

248
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:56,532
You're Genzo, right?

249
00:10:56,615 --> 00:10:57,616
Huh?

250
00:10:58,534 --> 00:10:59,535
And who are you?

251
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:02,246
I'm from the Meiwa team.

252
00:11:03,497 --> 00:11:05,082
I'm Kojiro Hyuga.

253
00:11:05,415 --> 00:11:07,501
So you're...Kojiro?

254
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:09,586
I've come to challenge you!

255
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:11,004
What?!

256
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:14,383
Huh?

257
00:11:14,508 --> 00:11:15,759
Coach, look over there.

258
00:11:17,469 --> 00:11:18,470
Teppei!

259
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,472
-Got it! Thanks!
-No way!

260
00:11:20,597 --> 00:11:22,558
I'll be the one to score
the first goal!

261
00:11:22,683 --> 00:11:24,268
-Huh?
-What the--?!

262
00:11:27,271 --> 00:11:28,522
Get ready, keeper!

263
00:11:30,732 --> 00:11:32,401
I'm going to crush you!

264
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:34,069
-That's Kojiro!
-What?

265
00:11:34,236 --> 00:11:35,404
Don't tell me that's...

266
00:11:35,404 --> 00:11:37,531
That's Kojiro, the captain
of the Meiwa team!

267
00:11:37,698 --> 00:11:39,116
What do we do now, Captain?

268
00:11:39,241 --> 00:11:40,242
Calm down!

269
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:41,869
I'll accept his challenge.

270
00:11:42,369 --> 00:11:44,037
Coach, we should stop this now.

271
00:11:46,415 --> 00:11:48,709
So that's him.
He is Kojiro.

272
00:11:50,752 --> 00:11:52,421
Hey, who do you
think you are

273
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:54,381
to come here and
ruin our training?!

274
00:11:55,257 --> 00:11:57,384
Beat it, fool!

275
00:11:57,509 --> 00:11:58,552
Hey, what's wrong with you?!

276
00:11:58,719 --> 00:12:00,846
Shutetsu!
Stop him now!

277
00:12:05,976 --> 00:12:07,978
Now I get what
you were talking about.

278
00:12:08,353 --> 00:12:10,606
His style really is
very different.

279
00:12:11,106 --> 00:12:13,483
That's right. If we think of
you as kind when playing,

280
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:15,903
then Kojiro is the most
aggressive player there is.

281
00:12:16,028 --> 00:12:17,779
What are you doing,
Shutetsu?!

282
00:12:17,905 --> 00:12:19,781
Stop that terrible bully
now!

283
00:12:19,907 --> 00:12:21,200
Go get him, Shingo!

284
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:23,535
I'll trust you'll be able to
knock some sense into him.

285
00:12:23,702 --> 00:12:24,703
Yeah!

286
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:31,710
Why did you hit him?!

287
00:12:31,835 --> 00:12:33,253
You did that on purpose!

288
00:12:33,378 --> 00:12:34,296
Hey, shut up!

289
00:12:34,421 --> 00:12:36,381
My game style is not
lame and pathetic

290
00:12:36,507 --> 00:12:37,841
like all of yours!

291
00:12:38,884 --> 00:12:40,385
Get ready, keeper!

292
00:12:41,512 --> 00:12:44,348
Let's see if your reputation
is as good as they say

293
00:12:44,348 --> 00:12:46,391
or you're just a fraud!

294
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:49,102
Watch out, Genzo!
Stop the ball!

295
00:13:06,370 --> 00:13:07,371
That's the goal keeper

296
00:13:07,371 --> 00:13:09,289
everyone keeps
yapping about?

297
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:11,708
You couldn't even react
to my shot.

298
00:13:11,834 --> 00:13:13,001
That's so pathetic.

299
00:13:15,379 --> 00:13:16,004
What's up?

300
00:13:16,088 --> 00:13:17,714
Tsubasa, I understand
how you feel,

301
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,299
but you should not
fight him now.

302
00:13:23,262 --> 00:13:24,096
Taro?

303
00:13:24,221 --> 00:13:25,222
Hey, Kojiro.

304
00:13:25,514 --> 00:13:27,391
Long time no see, Taro.

305
00:13:27,891 --> 00:13:31,228
Hey, don't tell me
you moved to this town.

306
00:13:31,979 --> 00:13:32,604
You know what?

307
00:13:32,729 --> 00:13:34,898
If you're part of this team,
then you should...

308
00:13:35,357 --> 00:13:36,358
just tell them
that the winner

309
00:13:36,483 --> 00:13:37,609
of the national tournament

310
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:39,862
is going to be
the Meiwa team from Showa.

311
00:13:40,696 --> 00:13:41,697
See ya!

312
00:13:43,615 --> 00:13:46,368
Kojiro, if you came here
to spy on us...

313
00:13:46,743 --> 00:13:49,496
then you should have
stayed a little longer.

314
00:13:50,414 --> 00:13:52,916
Now you'll hav to go home
without watching...

315
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,502
the skills of Tsubasa Ozora.

316
00:13:57,296 --> 00:13:58,297
Captain...

317
00:14:05,262 --> 00:14:06,638
I can't believe it!

318
00:14:08,515 --> 00:14:10,392
How is it possible that Genzo lost
to that arrogant idiot?!

319
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,686
Genzo left the field
without saying a word.

320
00:14:13,353 --> 00:14:14,479
-Huh?
-Huh?

321
00:14:18,108 --> 00:14:19,109
Genzo!

322
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,321
CAPTAIN TSUBASA

323
00:14:22,404 --> 00:14:23,280
We'll be right back

324
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:25,073
with Captain Tsubasa!

325
00:14:30,204 --> 00:14:32,414
AFFILIATION: SHOWA FC
BIRTHDAY: AUGUST 17 HEIGHT: 158 CM

326
00:14:33,123 --> 00:14:35,042
I'm really sorry
for what happened.

327
00:14:35,959 --> 00:14:37,836
So then you hurt your leg?

328
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:39,546
That's why you
couldn't react

329
00:14:39,671 --> 00:14:41,298
to that crazy kid's shot.

330
00:14:41,465 --> 00:14:42,925
No, you're mistaken.

331
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:45,719
Even if I had been able to,
I probably couldn't have...

332
00:14:46,261 --> 00:14:47,346
stopped that shot.

333
00:14:47,638 --> 00:14:48,847
It was too powerful.

334
00:14:49,598 --> 00:14:50,140
Oh...

335
00:14:50,307 --> 00:14:51,600
Besides...

336
00:14:51,767 --> 00:14:55,854
I will not use my injury
to avoid my responsibility.

337
00:14:56,104 --> 00:14:57,105
I lost.

338
00:14:57,147 --> 00:14:59,149
Tsubasa,
surely we'll go together

339
00:14:59,274 --> 00:15:00,108
to the national tournament,

340
00:15:00,275 --> 00:15:02,736
and I bet that Kojiro
will also be there.

341
00:15:03,111 --> 00:15:05,405
I'll get my reputation back
when I fight him.

342
00:15:05,739 --> 00:15:06,907
Ah!

343
00:15:07,074 --> 00:15:08,075
Yeah!

344
00:15:25,801 --> 00:15:27,219
Hello, good morning, son.

345
00:15:27,553 --> 00:15:28,554
Good morning.

346
00:15:28,846 --> 00:15:30,472
Will you work all day
today again, Mom?

347
00:15:30,556 --> 00:15:31,807
Son, don't you
worry about me.

348
00:15:31,932 --> 00:15:32,724
I'll be all right.

349
00:15:32,850 --> 00:15:35,352
I just want you to go and
enjoy your favorite sport.

350
00:15:35,936 --> 00:15:37,145
I will, Mom!

351
00:15:37,271 --> 00:15:38,856
My life is set on soccer!

352
00:15:40,732 --> 00:15:41,775
Since Dad died,

353
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,986
my mom has had to take
several jobs.

354
00:15:44,278 --> 00:15:47,698
I can't enjoy playing soccer
and watch my family suffer.

355
00:15:47,865 --> 00:15:49,074
SAKAMOTO GREEN GROCER

356
00:15:49,074 --> 00:15:50,075
Good morning!

357
00:15:50,576 --> 00:15:51,577
Would you like some help?

358
00:15:51,785 --> 00:15:53,120
Thank so much, kid!

359
00:15:53,287 --> 00:15:54,204
Be careful, though.
It's heavy!

360
00:15:54,204 --> 00:15:56,164
It's okay. I'll use it
as training, sir.

361
00:15:58,375 --> 00:16:00,169
I need to earn
all the money I can

362
00:16:00,294 --> 00:16:02,379
for when my siblings
get older.

363
00:16:03,338 --> 00:16:04,256
I'll need even more

364
00:16:04,256 --> 00:16:06,258
if I want to make it
to high school.

365
00:16:06,842 --> 00:16:08,385
But my siblings are first.

366
00:16:09,928 --> 00:16:11,346
Here.
Thank you very much.

367
00:16:11,889 --> 00:16:13,223
Thank you, sir.

368
00:16:13,849 --> 00:16:15,601
I'll become
a professional player

369
00:16:15,767 --> 00:16:17,686
and I'll take
my family along with me.

370
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:19,479
I won't let them
struggle anymore.

371
00:16:19,605 --> 00:16:21,106
They are my priority.

372
00:16:21,148 --> 00:16:23,233
That's why I have to
get better

373
00:16:23,358 --> 00:16:24,610
as a soccer player.

374
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,487
I must win
all the games I can

375
00:16:27,613 --> 00:16:29,948
and qualify for
the national tournament!

376
00:16:34,203 --> 00:16:35,871
Hey, Big Brother.
Good morning.

377
00:16:35,954 --> 00:16:38,040
Good morning!
I see you're already up!

378
00:16:38,373 --> 00:16:40,209
Big Brother, did Mom leave?

379
00:16:40,375 --> 00:16:41,877
Yeah, but don't worry.

380
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,086
I'll make breakfast today.

381
00:16:46,882 --> 00:16:49,218
Well, family, today,
I'll embark on another trip.

382
00:16:49,426 --> 00:16:51,136
Now that you decided
to go to Brazil,

383
00:16:51,136 --> 00:16:53,889
I probably won't see you
when I get back, son.

384
00:16:54,223 --> 00:16:56,225
So please, take care
and train hard.

385
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:57,100
I will!

386
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:58,268
Actually, Captain,

387
00:16:58,268 --> 00:16:59,978
Tsubasa promised me something

388
00:17:00,062 --> 00:17:01,355
before going to Brazil.

389
00:17:02,105 --> 00:17:02,773
And what is that?

390
00:17:02,898 --> 00:17:05,275
That if he doesn't win
the national tournament,

391
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:07,903
then he won't be able to
come with me to Brazil.

392
00:17:08,237 --> 00:17:09,613
That's quite a challenge!

393
00:17:09,738 --> 00:17:11,990
But I don't think there
will be any problem!

394
00:17:12,199 --> 00:17:14,993
I'm sure my little
soccer player will get it!

395
00:17:15,285 --> 00:17:16,662
Thanks, Dad!
Really!

396
00:17:17,037 --> 00:17:18,163
Listen, Tsubasa,

397
00:17:18,163 --> 00:17:20,207
I want you to promise me
something too.

398
00:17:20,916 --> 00:17:21,917
Huh?

399
00:17:22,417 --> 00:17:24,795
If you can score three goals
on today's game,

400
00:17:24,962 --> 00:17:27,339
then I'll let you
go to Brazil, got it?

401
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:28,465
I thought you said
that he could

402
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:30,217
go to Brazil already,
though, huh?

403
00:17:30,592 --> 00:17:32,219
Yes, darling, but I need to
make sure of

404
00:17:32,219 --> 00:17:33,887
his commitment to the trip.

405
00:17:34,596 --> 00:17:35,639
Of course, Dad!

406
00:17:35,722 --> 00:17:38,141
I'll do my very best to
score those three goals!

407
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:41,228
And I'll make sure to get
the moment on tape!

408
00:17:42,104 --> 00:17:44,106
The way it seems,
it looks like this might be

409
00:17:44,231 --> 00:17:46,108
the last game
of Tsubasa in Japan.

410
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:47,234
Hmm...

411
00:17:48,193 --> 00:17:48,277
MEIWA ELEMENTARY

412
00:17:48,277 --> 00:17:49,111
MEIWA ELEMENTARY
Captain, wait for me!

413
00:17:49,111 --> 00:17:49,403
Captain, wait for me!

414
00:17:50,904 --> 00:17:52,698
Please, Kojiro, don't go.

415
00:17:52,781 --> 00:17:55,117
Are you really not going
to be in the play-offs?

416
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,120
What? Didn't I
tell you to play and win

417
00:17:58,245 --> 00:18:00,163
the national tournament
on your own?

418
00:18:01,373 --> 00:18:02,374
I mean...

419
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:04,126
since you don't
want me to play,

420
00:18:04,376 --> 00:18:06,211
let's see how you do it
on your own.

421
00:18:08,172 --> 00:18:10,132
Why is he always
so stubborn?

422
00:18:10,174 --> 00:18:11,717
Now what are we gonna do?

423
00:18:11,925 --> 00:18:13,302
We can't win without him.

424
00:18:13,594 --> 00:18:15,470
I don't understand why
he is risking everything

425
00:18:15,596 --> 00:18:16,763
knowing what he got
on the line.

426
00:18:16,889 --> 00:18:18,599
-Doesn't he care?
-What's on the line?

427
00:18:18,807 --> 00:18:20,475
Well, it's just that
I heard that

428
00:18:20,601 --> 00:18:22,436
the captain's dad
died last year.

429
00:18:24,229 --> 00:18:25,397
Yeah and that's not all...

430
00:18:26,356 --> 00:18:27,900
I heard his mom has
several jobs now

431
00:18:27,983 --> 00:18:30,402
to provide for the captain
and all his siblings.

432
00:18:30,569 --> 00:18:32,279
I don't know why he risks
everything like that.

433
00:18:32,946 --> 00:18:34,781
Captain Kojiro needs
to win the tournament

434
00:18:34,907 --> 00:18:36,658
to become
a professional player.

435
00:18:37,367 --> 00:18:39,161
He only thinks about
finding a way

436
00:18:39,286 --> 00:18:40,454
to help his mother
with this.

437
00:18:40,579 --> 00:18:41,580
I understand!

438
00:18:41,788 --> 00:18:43,123
He has to win because
there'll be

439
00:18:43,248 --> 00:18:45,167
tons of scouts
in the national tournament!

440
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:46,168
If that's the case,

441
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:47,961
then we can't let him down!

442
00:18:48,212 --> 00:18:49,338
We have to win for him!

443
00:18:49,463 --> 00:18:50,464
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

444
00:18:52,508 --> 00:18:54,718
Finally,
all the teams have gathered

445
00:18:54,843 --> 00:18:56,970
to start
the national tournament.

446
00:18:57,888 --> 00:19:00,474
I made it at the end!

447
00:19:01,058 --> 00:19:03,268
All right, Genzo,
let's do our best.

448
00:19:03,268 --> 00:19:04,937
Yes, I will!
Let's do it!

449
00:19:05,354 --> 00:19:06,271
How's your leg feeling?

450
00:19:06,855 --> 00:19:09,233
It's better now. That's why
I'm here, Tsubasa.

451
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:11,068
Ladies and gentlemen,

452
00:19:11,151 --> 00:19:12,444
the third match of
the first round will be

453
00:19:12,444 --> 00:19:13,320
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT
SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT, DAY 1 ROUND 1

454
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:17,115
NANKATSU SC FUJI FCbetween the Nankatsu SC and the Fuji FC.

455
00:19:17,241 --> 00:19:18,700
This is your first match.

456
00:19:19,076 --> 00:19:20,369
Give it your best!

457
00:19:20,452 --> 00:19:21,453
-Yes!
-Yes!

458
00:19:23,205 --> 00:19:25,707
Come on!
Why am I benched?

459
00:19:27,376 --> 00:19:28,502
Tsubasa!

460
00:19:28,877 --> 00:19:30,087
We're here to support you!

461
00:19:30,420 --> 00:19:31,338
Dad!

462
00:19:31,463 --> 00:19:33,715
Remember!
I want three goals!

463
00:19:34,049 --> 00:19:35,050
Yeah!

464
00:19:37,719 --> 00:19:39,096
Tsubasa!

465
00:19:39,221 --> 00:19:41,265
You are truly the best!

466
00:19:42,599 --> 00:19:44,059
And the Nankatsu team

467
00:19:44,142 --> 00:19:45,143
makes the first move.

468
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:47,437
Just you wait.

469
00:19:48,355 --> 00:19:50,440
I'll show everyone
my skills.

470
00:19:51,108 --> 00:19:52,860
When the scouts see
what I can do,

471
00:19:52,943 --> 00:19:54,778
they will want me
and I'll become

472
00:19:54,903 --> 00:19:57,072
a professional
soccer player!

473
00:19:58,657 --> 00:20:00,158
And there it goes!

474
00:20:00,284 --> 00:20:02,578
The first goal
of Nankatsu!

475
00:20:02,703 --> 00:20:04,204
That's right!
One down!

476
00:20:06,248 --> 00:20:09,751
My destiny is in MY hands.

477
00:20:13,505 --> 00:20:16,300
And Nankatsu
scores its second goal!

478
00:20:21,847 --> 00:20:24,224
Now Tsubasa is heading
straight for the goal!

479
00:20:24,349 --> 00:20:26,977
And to think that I was
worried about my leg.

480
00:20:27,102 --> 00:20:29,438
At this pace, I won't
even have to move at all.

481
00:20:29,771 --> 00:20:31,773
Go for the third, Tsubasa!

482
00:20:31,899 --> 00:20:33,400
Go Tsubasa!

483
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:36,069
Pay attention!
I want you to stop him!

484
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:43,869
Tsubasa
makes a one-two pass

485
00:20:43,952 --> 00:20:45,204
to Taro Misaki!

486
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:48,207
Yeah! You better know
the golden duet!

487
00:20:48,582 --> 00:20:51,251
Tsubasa
gets ready and strikes!

488
00:20:51,376 --> 00:20:52,252
And goal!

489
00:20:52,252 --> 00:20:54,213
The keeper didn't even
see it coming!

490
00:20:54,338 --> 00:20:57,216
Tsubasa manages to get
a Hat-trick on this match!

491
00:20:57,341 --> 00:20:59,635
-Unbelievable!
-Dad! I did it! Did you see?

492
00:20:59,968 --> 00:21:01,053
That's amazing!

493
00:21:01,303 --> 00:21:04,097
Now I can get to the docks
as the proud father I am!

494
00:21:04,264 --> 00:21:06,391
I want you to win
the national tournament,

495
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:07,976
go to Brazil
to acheive your dream

496
00:21:08,101 --> 00:21:09,603
and become
a professional player!

497
00:21:10,103 --> 00:21:10,979
Yeah!

498
00:21:11,104 --> 00:21:13,065
Take care, Dad.
I love you!

499
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,151
Sail carefully.

500
00:21:16,318 --> 00:21:18,403
Yes, honey.
I promise you I will.

501
00:21:20,113 --> 00:21:20,197
NANKATSU SC FUJI FC MOVING ON TO THE SECOND ROUND

502
00:21:20,197 --> 00:21:24,076
NANKATSU SC FUJI FC MOVING ON TO THE SECOND ROUND
Final score, Nankatsu SC 7, Fuji FC 0.

503
00:21:24,076 --> 00:21:24,243
NANKATSU SC FUJI FC MOVING ON TO THE SECOND ROUND

504
00:21:26,286 --> 00:21:28,705
Hello, my son.
Why are you outside?

505
00:21:30,874 --> 00:21:31,875
Welcome home, Mom.

506
00:21:32,668 --> 00:21:34,253
I made your dinner
so you can eat.

507
00:21:34,878 --> 00:21:35,879
But it's late.

508
00:21:36,129 --> 00:21:37,798
Don't you have
a soccer match tomorrow?

509
00:21:38,131 --> 00:21:40,050
Yeah, but don't worry.
They'll win for me.

510
00:21:40,592 --> 00:21:41,969
But why won't you play?

511
00:21:42,052 --> 00:21:43,345
Oh!

512
00:21:45,222 --> 00:21:47,641
The Nankatsu team
won their first match.

513
00:21:47,808 --> 00:21:49,142
And continued
the winning streak

514
00:21:49,268 --> 00:21:51,061
in the following matches.

515
00:21:51,478 --> 00:21:52,646
On the other hand...

516
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:56,900
What a goal!

517
00:21:57,651 --> 00:21:59,444
I told you
we could do it!

518
00:21:59,570 --> 00:22:01,113
We did it!

519
00:22:01,238 --> 00:22:02,197
All right!

520
00:22:02,906 --> 00:22:04,116
This is bad.

521
00:22:04,241 --> 00:22:07,202
We barely won the last game,
but now, this is worse.

522
00:22:07,202 --> 00:22:08,161
Without the captain,

523
00:22:08,161 --> 00:22:10,205
it's practically impossible
to win.

524
00:22:14,751 --> 00:22:15,752
Captain...

525
00:22:23,468 --> 00:22:26,138
It looks like the team
needs my help, doesn't it?

526
00:22:26,346 --> 00:22:27,264
